title: DiNatale leads unbeaten Foran football to victory
text:
DiNatale leads unbeaten Foran football to victory Published 11:14 pm, Saturday, October 10, 2015 
Lance DiNatale was 17 for 23 for 342 yards and three touchdowns to lead Foran to a 55-18 win over Lyman Hall in an SCC contest Saturday. 
Jared Hubler had eight of those receptions for 182 yards and a score and also threw a touchdown pass, while RJ Balado carried 22 times for 133 yards and a score. 
Foran improved to 4-0 with the win. 
Also, Mike Bevino threw two touchdown passes and ran for another score to lead Notre Dame of Fairfield to its first win of the season 23-16 over Bethel.
